   <mods:abstract>Articles communicated to Congress by Minister of France which Spain wants
            precise information on: a precise and uniform boundary, exclusive navigation of the
            Mississippi, possession of the Floridas, lands on eastern side of the Mississippi. The
            U.S. should extend no farther westward than they have a right by the proclamation of
            1763. Since no U.S. territory situated on Mississippi River, the U.S. has no right to
            navigate the Mississippi. Since Spain will probably conquer the Floridas during the war
            all cause for difference between the U.S. and Spain in that area should be removed. The
            area next to Mississippi belongs to Britain, and Spain may conquer it during the war and
            the southern states should be prevented from making settlements there. The U.S. has not
            rights there as subjects of Britain. France hopes that America will accede to these
            demands.</mods:abstract>
